a magazines by circulation]]''. The best-selling manga magazine (and [[List of best-selling comic series|best-selling comic magazine]]) is ''[[Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump]]'', with over 7.5{{nbsp}}billion copies sold.<ref name=\"jump\">{{cite news |title=\u300c\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\u56f3\u66f8\u9928\u300d\u958b\u50ac\u300050\u5e74\u5206\u306e\u30b8\u30e3\u30f3\u30d7\u304c\u7121\u6599\u3067\u8aad\u3081\u308b |url=http://www.itmedia.co.jp/news/articles/1802/26/news098.html |work=ITmedia News |date=February 26, 2018 |language=ja |access-date=September 6, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180714193516/http://www.itmedia.co.jp/news/articles/1802/26/news098.html |archive-date=July 14, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Estimated circulation figures for individual manga series published in manga magazines are given in footnotes.{{efn|See ''{{Section link|Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump|Manga series}}'' for estimated circulation figures of individual manga series published in ''Weekly Sh\u014dnen Jump''.}}\n\n== Collected tank\u014dbon volumes ==\n[[File:One Piece, Volume 1.jpg|thumb|Cover of ''One Piece'' Vol. 1 (1997). ''[[One Piece]]'' is the best-selling manga series, having sold the most ''[[tank\u014dbon]]'' volumes.]]\n\n=== At least 100 million copies ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:#DFFFDF;\"|\n| Denotes manga series currently running\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Manga series !! Author(s) !! Publisher !! Demographic !! No. of collected<br>volumes !! Serialized !! Approximate sales\n|-style=\"background: #DFFFDF;\"\n||''[[One Piece]]'' || [[Eiichiro Oda]] || [[Shueisha]] || [[Sh\u014dnen manga|Sh\u014dnen]] ||95|| 1997\u2013present || 462{{nbsp}}million\u2020{{efn|''[[One Piece]]'' [[List of One Piece manga volumes|manga volume]] sales: {{formatnum:{{#expr:<!--FIRST 94 VOLUMES-->460000000+<!--VOLUME 95-->{{#expr:<!--WEEK 1-->883228+<!--WEEK 2-->568891+<!--WEEK 3-->163711+<!--WEEK 4-->69875+<!--WEEK 5-->42508