p (manga artists)|Clamp]] || Kodansha || Sh\u014dnen || 28 || 2003\u20132009 || 20 million<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2010-05-10/tsubasa-reservoir-chronicle-commemorative-day|title=Tsubasa Reservoir Chronicle Commemorative Day|publisher=Anime News Network|date=2009-05-10|accessdate=2013-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223083654/http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/press-release/2010-05-10/tsubasa-reservoir-chronicle-commemorative-day|archive-date=February 23, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Rookies (manga)|Rookies]]'' || [[Masanori Morita]] || Shueisha || Sh\u014dnen || 24 || 1998\u20132003 || 20 million<ref>[http://www.tbs.co.jp/program/rookies_20110808.html \u6708\u66dc\u30b4\u30fc\u30eb\u30c7\u30f3\u300e\u6620\u753b\u300cROOKIES-\u5352\u696d-\u300d\u300f] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190129181841/http://www.tbs.co.jp/program/rookies_20110808.html |date=January 29, 2019 }} TBS Television (August 2011)</ref>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of best-selling comic series]]\n*[[List of best-selling visual novels]]\n*[[List of highest-grossing media franchises]]\n*[[List of Japanese manga magazines by circulation]]\n*[[List of The New York Times Manga Best Sellers|List of ''The New York Times'' Manga Best Sellers]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=note}}\n{{notelist}}\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Media series}}\n\n{{reflist|group=upper-alpha}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of bestsellers|Manga]]\n[[Category:Lists of manga|Best-selling]]\n[[Category:Literature records]]\n", "name_user": "Katsuya", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBetween 20 million and 29 million copies", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_best-selling_manga"}
{"title_page": "Leona Evans", "text_new": "'''Leona Evans''' (born August 1, 1946) is an American Author <ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans|date= ||title= Amazon Author Profile |url= https://www.amazon.com/Leona-Evans/e/B001KC6LQE%3Fref=dbs_a_mng_rwt_scns_share |language= English|location= United States|publisher=}}</ref> \nand Actress. Ms. Evans appeared in various stage productions for over 30 years however is best known for her [[Amazon's Best Books of the Year | Amazon Bookseller 2017 Best Seller]] ''The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence''<ref>{{cite book |last=Evans |first=Leona |date= 2016 |title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= |language= English|location= United States|publisher=BalboaPress |isbn=978-1504370790|accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name          =  Leona Evans \n| image         =\n[[File:LE 2141 copy.jpg|frameless]]\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Leona Evans\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1946|08|01}}\n| birth_place   = [[Chicago, Illinois]], U.S.\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Writer/Actress\n| years_active  = 1951\u2013present\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n| website       = [http://www.wgifilms.org/ www.WGIFilms.org]\n}}\n\n== Early Life and Career ==\nBorn in [[Chicago |Chicago, Illinois,]] Evans began performing in the theater when she was four years old. During her 30 year career she appeared on [[Broadway theater | Broadway]], toured in National Companies of [[Fiddler on the Roof |Fiddler on the Roof]] and [[How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying (musical)|How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying]], and performed in Regional Theaters. Ms. Evans also toured for more than 15 years with her cabaret act and sang in major hotels and cabarets throughout the world. Since 1984 Evans has been a teacher and motivational speaker and has written two books on the importance of healthy self-esteem and the power of intention.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leona Evans, Amazon Author Profile |url=\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Leona-Evans/e/B001KC6LQE%3Fref=dbs_a_mng_rwt_scns_share}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Leona Evans, The Evolving PeaceMaker / Unity Worldwide Spiritual Institute |url=https://www.unityworldwideministries.org/uwsi/spiritual-explorers-evolving-peacemaker}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Leona Evans, Teaching People How to Heal / Hay House Radio |url= https://www.hayhouseradio.com/#!/episode/teach-with-passion}}</ref>\n\nIn 1985 she was ordained as a [[Unity Church | Unity]] Minister in San Luis Obispo, California and also holds certification in Con\ufb02ict Management and Peace building by the [[United States Institute of Peace |United States Institute of Peace]]. Ms. Evans holds a Master of Arts in Religious Studies and was a former Chair of the Metaphysics Department at [[Unity Church | Unity]] School for Religious Studies. Currently besides her duties as a minister she is a sought after speaker and teacher for radio, television, and podcasts worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leona Evans, The Evolving PeaceMaker / Unity Worldwide Spiritual Institute |url=https://www.unityworldwideministries.org/uwsi/spiritual-explorers-evolving-peacemaker}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Seven Essential Pathways Inner Peace / NAACP |url=http://naacpslocty.org/event/seven-essential-pathways-inner-peace-power-forgiveness/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Leona & Matthew J. Evans/ Unity Online Radio |url=https://www.unityonlineradio.org/evolving-peacemaker}}</ref>  Ms. Evan's son [[Matthew J. Evans | Matthew J. Evans]] is also a musician, \ufb01lmmaker, and actor. <ref>{{cite web|title=Matthew J. Evans, IMDb Profile |url=\nhttps://www.imdb.com/name/nm2298331/}}</ref>\n\n= Books | Awards | Interviews =\nIn 1992 Ms. Evans published her first book ''Nothing is too Good to be True.''<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans|date= 1992||title= Nothing is too Good to be True |url= https://www.amazon.com/Nothing-Too-Good-True-Fulfillment/dp/096337320X |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Institute for Self Awareness}}</ref> Then in 1999 she co-authored \"Spirituality & Self-Esteem\" with Carol Keefer.<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans & Carol Keefer|date= 1999||title= Spirituality & Self-Esteem |url=https://www.amazon.com/Spirituality-Self-Esteem-Carol-Keefer/dp/0963373218/|language= English|location= United States|publisher=Institute for Self Awareness| isbn=978-0963373212 |accessdate=}}</ref> In 2016 she published '' The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence''<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans |date= 2016||title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1504370791/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i0 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Balboa Press | isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref> Most recently in 2019 she co-authored with her son the E-Book,'' Before It's Too Late: An Essay on Spiritual Activism in a Politically Charged World.''<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans |date= 2019||title= Before It's Too Late: An Essay on Spiritual Activism in a Politically Charged World |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07TYXYXHR/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i1 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Amazon.com Services LLC | ASIN=B07TYXYXHR |accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Book\n!Publisher\n!Reference\n!Reviews\n|-\n|2019\n|'' Before It's Too Late: An Essay on Spiritual Activism in a Politically Charged World''\n|Kindle E-Book's\n|<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans |date= 2019||title= Before It's Too Late: An Essay on Spiritual Activism in a Politically Charged World |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07TYXYXHR/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i1 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Amazon.com Services LLC | ASIN=B07TYXYXHR |accessdate=}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|'' The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence''\n|Balboa Press \n|<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans |date= 2016||title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1504370791/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i0 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Balboa Press | isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref>\n|<ref>{{cite book|author= |date= 2016||title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/leona-evans/evolving-peacemaker |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Kirkus Reviews | isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite book|author =|date= 2016||title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= http://www.noveljunky.com/2017/07/review-evolving-peacemaker-commitment.html |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Novel Junky | isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite book|author =|date= 2016||title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= http://www.midwestbookreview.com/sbw/may_17.htm |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Small Press Bookwatch | isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author =|date= 2016||title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url=https://www.goodreads.com/en/book/show/33369450-the-evolving-peacemaker|language= English|location= United States|publisher=GoodReads| isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref>\n|-\n|1999\n|''Spirituality & Self-Esteem''\n|Institute for Self Awareness\n|<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans & Carol Keefer|date= 1999||title= Spirituality & Self-Esteem |url=https://www.amazon.com/Spirituality-Self-Esteem-Carol-Keefer/dp/0963373218/|language= English|location= United States|publisher=Institute for Self Awareness| isbn=978-0963373212 |accessdate=}}</ref>\n|-\n|1992\n|''Nothing is too Good to be True''\n|Institute for Self Awareness\n|<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans|date= 1992||title= Nothing is too Good to be True |url= https://www.amazon.com/Nothing-Too-Good-True-Fulfillment/dp/096337320X |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Institute for Self Awareness}}</ref> \n|\n|}\n=== Awards for The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence===\n* [[Amazon's Best Books of the Year | 2017 Amazon Bookseller Best Seller]] <ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans  |date= 2016|title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1504370791/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i0 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Balboa Press | isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n* 2017 Evergreen Medal for World Peace by the Living Now Book Awards <ref name=\"2017 Evergreen Medal for World Peace by the Living Now Book Awards\">{{cite web|title= 2017 Evergreen Medal for World Peace by the Living Now Book Awards| url=http://www.livingnowawards.com/135/2017-evergreen-winners| website=Living Now Awards|date= 2017|accessdate=}}</ref> \n\n* 2017 Personal Growth & Self-Help: Motivational categories by Beverly Hills Book Awards<ref name=\"2017 Personal Growth & Self-Help: Motivational categories by Beverly Hills Book Awards\">{{cite web|title= 2018 Beverly Hills Book Awards| url=https://www.beverlyhillsbookawards.com/6th-BHBA-Winners-and-Finalists.htm| website=Beverly Hills Book Awards|date= 2018|accessdate=}}</ref> \n\n* 2017 Gold Medal at the eLit Book Awards in the Inspirational/Spiritual category<ref name=\"Gold medal at the eLit Book Awards in the Inspirational/Spiritual category\">{{cite web|title=  Elita Awards 2018 Results| url=http://www.elitawards.com/2018_results.php| website=Elita Awards|date= 2018|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n=== Interviews ===\n\n* ''SLO Journal / From Broadway to Gandhi (regional periodical)''(2017)<ref>{{cite periodical|title =Leona & Mathew J. Evans|date= 2017||title= From Broadway to Gandhi / SLO Journal |url=https://issuu.com/journalplus/docs/5-17_journal_plus_web/8 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n* ''Lisa Haselton'' (2017) (award winning blog)<ref>{{cite periodical|title =Leona & Mathew J. Evans|date= 2017||title= Lisa Haselton Blog |url=\nhttp://lisahaseltonsreviewsandinterviews.blogspot.com/2017/01/interview-with-writer-leona-evans.html |language= English|location= United States|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n* ''Aspiring Hollywood/ Leona Evans interview (2011)''<ref>{{cite periodical|title =Leona Evans / Aspiring Hollywood|date= 2011||title= Leona Evans / Aspiring Hollywood|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G_SAZmbgFQM |language= English|location= United States|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n= Acting & Filmography =\nIn 2002 Evans worked in the movie version of [[Max_Lucado|Max Lucado's]] book, ''You Are Mine''<ref>{{cite web|author= Mark Swanson based on book by Max Lucado  |date= 2002||title= You Are Mine|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0820495/?ref_=nm_flmg_act_2|language= English|location= United States|publisher= Impact Productions}}</ref> Then in 2010 she narrated with her son; film actor and producer, Matthew Evan's first documentary short film, ''\"A War Story, A Love Story\".''  In 2012 she continued to work with her son in his short documentary film  ''A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions'' <ref>{{cite web|title= A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions  |date= 2012||title= A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2418812/?ref_=nm_knf_i4|language= English|location= United States|publisher= IMDb Database }}</ref> featuring interviews with [[Arun Manilal Gandhi |Arun Gandhi]]. In 2017 Ms. Evans worked with him one more time in their production ''Song of the Earth''<ref>{{cite web|author1= Leona Evans |author2= Matthew J. Evans|date= 2017|title= Song of the Earth: Improvisational Music & Narration|url= https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6930518/plotsummary?ref_=tt_ov_pl|language= English|location= United States|publisher= IMDb.com Database}}</ref> \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Documentaries / Features / Interviews\n|-\n!Year\n!Film\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|2017\n|''Song of the Earth'''<ref>{{cite web|author1= Leona Evans |author2= Matthew J. Evans|date= 2017|title= Song of the Earth: Improvisational Music & Narration|url= https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6930518/plotsummary?ref_=tt_ov_pl|language= English|location= United States|publisher= IMDb.com Database}}</ref> \n|Narrator\n|\n|-\n|2012\n|''A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions''<ref>{{cite web|title= A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions  |date= 2012||title= A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2418812/?ref_=nm_knf_i4|language= English|location= United States|publisher= }}</ref> \n|Narrator\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''Aspiring Hollywood''\n|Guest\n|\"Leona Evans Interview \"<ref>{{cite periodical|title =Leona Evans / Aspiring Hollywood|date= 2011||title= Leona Evans / Aspiring Hollywood|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G_SAZmbgFQM |language= English|location= United States|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n|2012\n|''A War Story, a Love Story  ''<ref>{{cite Web|title =A War Story, a Love Story |date= 2012||title= A War Story, a Love Story |url= https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1586685/?ref_=nm_flmg_slf_3 |language= English|location= United States|publisher= WGIFilms}}</ref>\n|Narrator\n|\n|-\n|2002\n|''You Are Mine''<ref>{{cite web|author=Mark Swanson based on book by Max Lucado  |date= 2002||title= You Are Mine|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0820495/?ref_=nm_flmg_act_2|language= English|location= United States|publisher= Impact Productions}}</ref> \n|Mayors Wife -(voice)\n|\n|}\n== Synopsis ==\n* '''Song of the Earth [2017]'''<ref>{{cite web|author=|date= 2017|title= Song of the Earth|url= https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6930518/plotsummary?ref_=tt_ov_pl|language= English|location= United States|publisher= IMDb.com Database}}</ref>  - a moving narration of the hero's journey depicted in poetry and improvisational music. Produced, directed, and performed by young filmmaker and musician [[ Matthew J. Evans | Matthew J. Evans]], this experimental short takes us on a visual journey that embraces the unity of all life and instills hope for our future.<br>\n* '''A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions[2012]'''<ref>{{cite web|title= A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions  |date= 2012||title= A Quest For Peace: Nonviolence Among Religions|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2418812/?ref_=nm_knf_i4|language= English|location= United States|publisher= }}</ref> -Young filmmaker, [[ Matthew J. Evans | Matthew J. Evans]], takes a look at one of the most pressing issues in our modern society: violence among religions.  Through discussions with [[Arun Manilal Gandhi |Arun Gandhi]], grandson of [[M.K. Gandhi |Mahatma Gandhi]], and local religious leaders from the [[Central Coast (California)]], Matthew learns powerful lessons about nonviolence, acceptance, and cultural understanding. As [[M.K. Gandhi |Mahatma Gandhi]] has said, 'We must become the change we wish to see in our world!' This film helps us understand how we can make these changes.\n* '''A War Story, a Love Story [2012]''' <ref>{{cite Web|title =A War Story, a Love Story |date= 2012||title= A War Story, a Love Story |url= https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1586685/?ref_=nm_flmg_slf_3 |language= English|location= United States|publisher= WGIFilms}}</ref>- A married couple, celebrating their 60th wedding anniversary, relive their experiences during the [[Korean War| Korean War]]. Included in the film are historic photos and relevant information about what has been referred to as 'the Forgotten War', as well as powerful and poignant moments that remind us of the love that endures through separation and hardship.\n\n= References =\n", "text_old": "'''Leona Evans''' (born August 1, 1946) is an American Author <ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans|date= ||title= Amazon Author Profile |url= https://www.amazon.com/Leona-Evans/e/B001KC6LQE%3Fref=dbs_a_mng_rwt_scns_share |language= English|location= United States|publisher=}}</ref> \nand Actress. Ms. Evans appeared in various stage productions for over 30 years however is best known for her [[Amazon's Best Books of the Year | Amazon Bookseller 2017 Best Seller]] ''The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence''<ref>{{cite book |last=Evans |first=Leona |date= 2016 |title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= |language= English|location= United States|publisher=BalboaPress |isbn=978-1504370790|accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name          =  Leona Evans \n| image         =\n[[File:LE 2141 copy.jpg|frameless]]\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Leona Evans\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1946|08|01}}\n| birth_place   = [[Chicago, Illinois]], U.S.\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Writer/Actress\n| years_active  = 1951\u2013present\n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n| website       = [http://www.wgifilms.org/ www.WGIFilms.org]\n}}\n\n== Early Life and Career ==\nBorn in [[Chicago |Chicago, Illinois,]] Evans began performing in the theater when she was four years old. During her 30 year career she appeared on [[Broadway theater | Broadway]], toured in National Companies of [[Fiddler on the Roof |Fiddler on the Roof]] and [[How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying (musical)|How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying]], and performed in Regional Theaters. Ms. Evans also toured for more than 15 years with her cabaret act and sang in major hotels and cabarets throughout the world. Since 1984 Evans has been a teacher and motivational speaker and has written two books on the importance of healthy self-esteem and the power of intention.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leona Evans, Amazon Author Profile |url=\nhttps://www.amazon.com/Leona-Evans/e/B001KC6LQE%3Fref=dbs_a_mng_rwt_scns_share}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Leona Evans, The Evolving PeaceMaker / Unity Worldwide Spiritual Institute |url=https://www.unityworldwideministries.org/uwsi/spiritual-explorers-evolving-peacemaker}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Leona Evans, Teaching People How to Heal / Hay House Radio |url= https://www.hayhouseradio.com/#!/episode/teach-with-passion}}</ref>\n\nIn 1985 she was ordained as a [[Unity Church | Unity]] Minister in San Luis Obispo, California and also holds certification in Con\ufb02ict Management and Peace building by the [[United States Institute of Peace |United States Institute of Peace]]. Ms. Evans holds a Master of Arts in Religious Studies and was a former Chair of the Metaphysics Department at [[Unity Church | Unity]] School for Religious Studies. Currently besides her duties as a minister she is a sought after speaker and teacher for radio, television, and podcasts worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|title=Leona Evans, The Evolving PeaceMaker / Unity Worldwide Spiritual Institute |url=https://www.unityworldwideministries.org/uwsi/spiritual-explorers-evolving-peacemaker}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Seven Essential Pathways Inner Peace / NAACP |url=http://naacpslocty.org/event/seven-essential-pathways-inner-peace-power-forgiveness/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Leona & Matthew J. Evans/ Unity Online Radio |url=https://www.unityonlineradio.org/evolving-peacemaker}}</ref>  Ms. Evan's son [[Matthew J. Evans | Matthew J. Evans]] is also a musician, \ufb01lmmaker, and actor. <ref>{{cite web|title=Matthew J. Evans, IMDb Profile |url=\nhttps://www.imdb.com/name/nm2298331/}}</ref>\n\n= Books | Awards | Interviews =\nIn 1992 Ms. Evans published her first book ''Nothing is too Good to be True.''<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans|date= 1992||title= Nothing is too Good to be True |url= https://www.amazon.com/Nothing-Too-Good-True-Fulfillment/dp/096337320X |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Institute for Self Awareness}}</ref> Then in 1999 she co-authored \"Spirituality & Self-Esteem\" with Carol Keefer.<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans & Carol Keefer|date= 1999||title= Spirituality & Self-Esteem |url=https://www.amazon.com/Spirituality-Self-Esteem-Carol-Keefer/dp/0963373218/|language= English|location= United States|publisher=Institute for Self Awareness| isbn=978-0963373212 |accessdate=}}</ref> In 2016 she published '' The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence''<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans |date= 2016||title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1504370791/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i0 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Balboa Press | isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref> Most recently in 2019 she co-authored with her son the E-Book,'' Before It's Too Late: An Essay on Spiritual Activism in a Politically Charged World.''<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans |date= 2019||title= Before It's Too Late: An Essay on Spiritual Activism in a Politically Charged World |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07TYXYXHR/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i1 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Amazon.com Services LLC | ASIN=B07TYXYXHR |accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Book\n!Publisher\n!Reference\n!Reviews\n|-\n|2019\n|'' Before It's Too Late: An Essay on Spiritual Activism in a Politically Charged World''\n|Kindle E-Book's\n|<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans |date= 2019||title= Before It's Too Late: An Essay on Spiritual Activism in a Politically Charged World |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B07TYXYXHR/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i1 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Amazon.com Services LLC | ASIN=B07TYXYXHR |accessdate=}}</ref>\n|-\n|2016\n|'' The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence''\n|Balboa Press \n|<ref>{{cite book|author=Leona Evans |date= 2016||title= The Evolving Peacemaker: A Commitment to Nonviolence |url= https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1504370791/ref=dbs_a_def_rwt_bibl_vppi_i0 |language= English|location= United States|publisher=Balboa Press | isbn=978-1504370790 |accessdate=}}</ref>\n|<ref>{{cite book|author= |date= 2016|